article.description: Chase Fischer scored 21 points, Kyle Davis and Kyle Collinsworth added 15 apiece, and BYU's defense tightened up after a loose first half to hang on for a 73-68 win over Weber State on Saturday.
article.headline: Fischer, tight defense late lead BYU over Weber State 73-68
article.linkText: Fischer, tight defense late lead BYU over Weber State 73-68
article.story: SALT LAKE CITY -- Chase Fischer scored 21 points, Kyle Davis and Kyle Collinsworth added 15 apiece, and BYU's defense tightened up after a loose first half to hang on for a 73-68 win over Weber State on Saturday. Fischer was 7 of 12 from the field and made four 3-pointers for BYU (5-2), adding five rebounds and four steals. Collinsworth hit two jump shots late, pushing the Cougars' lead back to eight points each time. BYU made just 5 of 10 free-throw attempts in the final 1:09. Weber State (5-3) made 15 of its first 20 shots and finished the first half shooting at a 67 percent clip. But the Wildcats had four quick turnovers out of the break, and BYU used a 9-2 run to take a 48-39 lead. Jeremy Senglin had 20 points and five assists for the Wildcats. BYU played without freshman Nick Emery, who was suspended one game after punching Brandon Taylor during Wednesday's 83-75 loss at Utah.
